# Linear Regressioin
# Data:
# X(week)                                            v(sales in thousand)
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1                                                             1.2
# 2                                                             1.8
# 3                                                             2.5
# 4                                                             3.2
# 5                                                             3.8

# Linear regression formula --> y = a0+a1*x
# a1-->((meanof(x*y)) - (x*y))/meanof(x^2) - (meanof(x)^2)
# a0 = mean(y) - a1*meanof(x)
#        x         y              x^2                x^y
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
#        1        1.2              1                 1.2
#        2        1.8              4                 3.6
#        3        2.5              9                 7.5
#        4        3.2              16                12.8
#        5        3.8              25                19
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
#   sum: 15       12.5             55                44.4
#  Average: x=3    y=2.5           11                 8.88

# 1.) x=3, y=2.5, meanof(x^2)=11, meanof(xy)=8.88
# a1 = (8.88-(3*2-52))/11-3^2==>0.66
# a0 = 2.52-(0.66*3) = 0.54

# The sales of 3rd week
# y = a0+(a1*x)
# y = 0.54+(0.66*3)
# y = 2.52

# The sales of 7th week
# y = 0.54+(0.66*7)
# y = 5.16
